text: Len Rossi (born Len Rositano; September 24, 1929 â€“ October 9, 2020) was an American professional wrestler. He competed throughout the National Wrestling Alliance from 1958 to 1972. Rossi was also a member of both the NWA Hall of Fame in 2016 and the Professional Wrestling Hall of Fame in 2004. He was born in Utica, New York.
